column1: # This file was produced by the NASA Exoplanet Archive
# https://exoplanetarchive.ipac.caltech.edu
# Based on Kepler Objects of Interest (KOI) Q1–Q17 DR25 cumulative table
# Identification Columns
# COLUMN kepid: Kepler Identification (KepID). Unique target star ID from Kepler Input Catalog (KIC).
# COLUMN kepoi_name: KOI Name. Identifier in format KNNNNN.DD (e.g.
# COLUMN kepler_name: Kepler Name. Assigned name (e.g.
# Disposition Columns
# COLUMN koi_disposition: Exoplanet Archive Disposition. One of CONFIRMED
# COLUMN koi_pdisposition: Disposition Using Kepler Data. Pipeline classification (CANDIDATE
# COLUMN koi_score: Disposition Score (0–1). Confidence in the KOI classification from Monte Carlo runs.
# COLUMN koi_fpflag_nt: Not Transit-Like Flag. 1 = light curve not consistent with a planet transit.
# COLUMN koi_fpflag_ss: Stellar Eclipse Flag. 1 = likely eclipsing binary or stellar variability.
# COLUMN koi_fpflag_co: Centroid Offset Flag. 1 = signal likely from a nearby star.
# COLUMN koi_fpflag_ec: Ephemeris Match Indicates Contamination Flag. 1 = signal matches period/epoch of another source.
# Transit Properties
# COLUMN koi_period: Orbital Period [days]. Interval between consecutive transits.
# COLUMN koi_period_err1: Orbital Period Upper Uncertainty [days].
# COLUMN koi_period_err2: Orbital Period Lower Uncertainty [days].
# COLUMN koi_time0bk: Transit Epoch [BKJD]. First detected transit midpoint (BJD – 2454833.0).
# COLUMN koi_time0bk_err1: Transit Epoch Upper Uncertainty [BKJD].
# COLUMN koi_time0bk_err2: Transit Epoch Lower Uncertainty [BKJD].
# COLUMN koi_impact: Impact Parameter. Projected distance (in stellar radii) between star and planet centers during transit.
# COLUMN koi_impact_err1: Impact Parameter Upper Uncertainty.
# COLUMN koi_impact_err2: Impact Parameter Lower Uncertainty.
# COLUMN koi_duration: Transit Duration [hours].
# COLUMN koi_duration_err1: Transit Duration Upper Uncertainty [hours].
# COLUMN koi_duration_err2: Transit Duration Lower Uncertainty [hours].
# COLUMN koi_depth: Transit Depth [ppm]. Fractional stellar flux lost during transit.
# COLUMN koi_depth_err1: Transit Depth Upper Uncertainty [ppm].
# COLUMN koi_depth_err2: Transit Depth Lower Uncertainty [ppm].
# COLUMN koi_prad: Planetary Radius [Earth radii].
# COLUMN koi_prad_err1: Planetary Radius Upper Uncertainty [Earth radii].
# COLUMN koi_prad_err2: Planetary Radius Lower Uncertainty [Earth radii].
# COLUMN koi_teq: Equilibrium Temperature [K]. Approximation assuming blackbody equilibrium.
# COLUMN koi_teq_err1: Equilibrium Temperature Upper Uncertainty [K].
# COLUMN koi_teq_err2: Equilibrium Temperature Lower Uncertainty [K].
# COLUMN koi_insol: Insolation Flux [Earth flux]. Relative stellar flux received compared to Earth.
# COLUMN koi_insol_err1: Insolation Flux Upper Uncertainty [Earth flux].
# COLUMN koi_insol_err2: Insolation Flux Lower Uncertainty [Earth flux].
# COLUMN koi_model_snr: Transit Signal-to-Noise Ratio. Depth normalized by mean flux uncertainty.
# TCE Information
# COLUMN koi_tce_plnt_num: TCE Planet Number. Index of planet candidate in system.
# COLUMN koi_tce_delivname: TCE Delivery Name. Internal Kepler pipeline delivery tag.
# Stellar Parameters
# COLUMN koi_steff: Stellar Effective Temperature [K].
# COLUMN koi_steff_err1: Stellar Effective Temperature Upper Uncertainty [K].
# COLUMN koi_steff_err2: Stellar Effective Temperature Lower Uncertainty [K].
# COLUMN koi_slogg: Stellar Surface Gravity [log10(cm/s^2)].
# COLUMN koi_slogg_err1: Stellar Surface Gravity Upper Uncertainty [log10(cm/s^2)].
# COLUMN koi_slogg_err2: Stellar Surface Gravity Lower Uncertainty [log10(cm/s^2)].
# COLUMN koi_srad: Stellar Radius [Solar radii].
# COLUMN koi_srad_err1: Stellar Radius Upper Uncertainty [Solar radii].
# COLUMN koi_srad_err2: Stellar Radius Lower Uncertainty [Solar radii].
# KIC Parameters
# COLUMN ra: Right Ascension [deg].
# COLUMN dec: Declination [deg].
# COLUMN koi_kepmag: Kepler-band Magnitude [mag].
